ion against the present world and its disasters.\n\n- Ross\n|\nReal poetry, is to lead a beautiful life. To live poetry is better than to write it.\n\n- Bashō\n|\nYour hair is winter fire,January embers.My heart burns there, too.-Stephen King, IT\n\n- Stephen\n|\nNo matter where you are, you're always a bit on your own, always an outsider.\n\n- Banana Yoshimoto, Goodbye Tsugumi\n|\nTime in the most powerful thing.Not money, not power, not hope.A person can have everything theydesire but without time they are,all useless.\n\n- Akash Lakhotia, World Hypnotized: Making of the Fuhrer\n|\nGet off me you dirty turnip!' 'Dirty turnip? well, pardon me Signor Cabbage-Head!\n\n- Elle Newmark, The Book of Unholy Mischief\n|\nI wanted to see the place where Margaret grew to what she is, even at the worst time of all, when I had no hope of ever calling her mine.\n\n- Elizabeth Gaskell, North and South\n|\nI think of my pile of old paperbacks, their pages gone wobbly, like they'd once belonged to the sea.\n\n- Kazuo Ishiguro, Never Let Me Go\n|\nFor a game, you don’t need a teacher.\n\n- Dejan Stojanovic, The Sun Watches the Sun\n|\nWe are condemned to be free people, liberated people who must make life-defining decisions. Freedom requires choices and all choices entail value decisions.\n\n- Kilroy J. Oldster, Dead Toad Scrolls\n|\nCOMPETITOR is one who can steal a few deals, but, the pinch of which, A VISIONARY Never feels...!\n\n- Sujit Lalwani, Life Simplified!\n|\nA humble heart, a friendly look, a smile on the face is really what you need to break the ice, not a very big axe.\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, Book of Wisdom\n|\nThe more you praise and celebrate your life, the more there is in life to celebrate.\n\n- Oprah\n|\nDeath? Why all this fuss about death? Use your imagination, try to visualize a world without death! Death is the essential condition to life, not an evil.\n\n- Charlotte\n|\nThey say when you are missing someone that they are probably feeling the same, but I